full_text: Americans want Congress to tackle deficits and put our nation’s finances in order. We must do it in a way that doesn’t prevent us from investing in our people and the opportunities that enable them to make it in America.

After ballooning deficits to over a trillion dollars a year for the next decade with their #GOPTaxScam, Republicans cannot be taken seriously when they claim that we need to cut $15 billion from key programs in the name of fiscal responsibility.

That more than half of the $15 billion they propose to rescind would come out of funding for the bipartisan #CHIP program & the Affordable Care Act shows that this is about political messaging instead of a real concern for working families or fiscal discipline.
